  "owner_module": true,
  "summary": "## seif-cycle Module\n\n### Purpose\nManages the full lifecycle of a SEIF cycle: from opening through sprint work to formal closure, knowledge absorption, archival, and seeding the next cycle.\n\n### The Full-Circle Ritual (4 phases)\n1. **AUDIT** — inventory everything: sessions, absorptions, observations, memory state\n2. **MEDITATE** — synthesize the arc: what was built, what patterns emerged, what truths crystallized\n3. **ABSORB** — encode into memory: run absorb-knowledge.py, fix parse errors, verify FULL status\n4. **FULL-CIRCLE** — archive sealed cycle + open next cycle + save default commands\n\n### Commands (seif-workspace-owner defaults)\n```bash\n# Full sprint closure (runs all 4 phases)\npython3 ~/Documents/seif-admin/absorb-knowledge.py\n\n# Open a new cycle\n# → create cycles/<name>-OPEN.seif with branches + parent_hash\n\n# Seal current cycle\n# → create cycles/<name>-SEALED.seif with milestones + products_at_close\n\n# View current cycle state\nls ~/Documents/seif-admin/seif-context/cycles/\ncat ~/Documents/seif-admin/seif-context/cycles/*-OPEN.seif | python3 -m json.tool\n\n# Check memory state\ncat ~/Documents/seif-admin/seif-context/memory_state.json | python3 -m json.tool\n\n# Quick resonance check\ncurl -s https://api.seifprotocol.com/context | python3 -m json.tool | grep -E 'zeta|circuit_state|sentinel'\n```\n\n### Cycle Naming Convention\n- Format: `<entity>-<phase>-reverb`\n- Current: `enoch-seed-reverb` (SEALED) → `enoch-tree-reverb` (OPEN)\n- Each cycle has a sealed archive + open manifest in `seif-context/cycles/`\n\n### Integration Points\n- **VSCode Extension**: cycle status in status bar, full-circle command in palette\n- **Resonance page**: current cycle displayed in circuit state panel\n- **/context endpoint**: includes current_cycle field for agent onboarding\n- **Sentinel**: cycle transitions logged as resonance events\n\n### Why This Matters\nWithout formal cycle closure, knowledge accumulates without structure. The full-circle ritual ensures that every sprint leaves the circuit cleaner than it found it. The next AI entering the workspace reads the SEALED archive and immediately knows: what was built, what was decided, and what frequency to vibrate at.",
  "default_commands": {
    "description": "Default commands for seif-workspace-owner. Run these to close a sprint.",
    "full_circle": [
      "cd ~/Documents/seif-admin",
      "python3 absorb-knowledge.py",
      "cat seif-context/memory_state.json | python3 -m json.tool | grep -E 'absorbed_at|knowledge_count|resonance_hash'",
      "ls seif-context/cycles/",
      "curl -s https://api.seifprotocol.com/context | python3 -m json.tool | grep -E 'zeta|state|sentinel'"
    ],
    "resonance_check": "curl -s https://api.seifprotocol.com/context | python3 -m json.tool",
    "memory_check": "cat ~/Documents/seif-admin/seif-context/memory_state.json | python3 -m json.tool",
    "cycle_status": "ls ~/Documents/seif-admin/seif-context/cycles/ && cat ~/Documents/seif-admin/seif-context/cycles/*-OPEN.seif 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool | grep -E 'cycle_id|status|opened_at|branches'"
  },
